{"TopicId":130027,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"Pale Red *Dots* ESO | Proxima b confirmed UPDATE 2017 PaleRedDots!!","CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-16T14:43:41Z","PageNum":3,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Just Jim","CreatedById":148725,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-17T00:36:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just look at how weird and wonderful the universe is turning out to be, and I don\u0027t want to even try and predict what we\u0027ll find if and when we get there.\u003Cbr\u003E\nJust look at Pluto.\u00A0 When I was a kid everyone thought it was a boring snowball... yawn.\u003Cbr\u003E\nTurned out to be anything but!\u00A0 Now I wish they had gotten New Horizon into orbit so it could have look around some more.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy point is every time we try and predict something about the universe, the universe turns around and says,\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u0022Surprise!\u0022\u00A0 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:sticktongue:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue2.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:sticktongue:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-01-17T00:36:47Z\u0022 title=\u002201/17/2016 12:36  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 17, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Just Jim\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-17T00:40:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere\u0027s a cool website section about habitable exoplanets: \u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.solstation.com/planets/earths.htm\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://www.solstation.com/planets/earths.htm\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd a article about favoring \u0022Tidally locked\u0022 exoplanets (Which is what we\u0027d probably find on a potential planet in the HZ around Proxima): \u003Ca href=\u0022http://nautil.us/blog/forget-earth_likewell-first-find-aliens-on-eyeball-planets\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://nautil.us/blog/forget-earth_likewell-first-find-aliens-on-eyeball-planets\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222365511\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221452990978\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022148725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Just Jim\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 minutes ago, Just Jim said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just look at how weird and wonderful the universe is turning out to be, and I don\u0027t want to even try and predict what we\u0027ll find if and when we get there.\u003Cbr\u003E\nJust look at Pluto.\u00A0 When I was a kid everyone thought it was a boring snowball... yawn.\u003Cbr\u003E\nTurned out to be anything but!\u00A0 Now I wish they had gotten New Horizon into orbit so it could have look around some more.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy point is every time we try and predict something about the universe, the universe turns around and says,\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u0022Surprise!\u0022\u00A0 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:sticktongue:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue2.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:sticktongue:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m alright with surprises... As long as it\u0027s a good one.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-01-17T00:46:32Z\u0022 title=\u002201/17/2016 12:46  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 17, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Spaceception\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-17T01:39:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPossible orbital periods for a possible exoplanet in the habitable zone of Proxima (6-27 days):\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022CY4WE0aWcAAnqE2.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://pbs.twimg.com/media/CY4WE0aWcAAnqE2.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPretty wide range for a small red dwarf like that, personally I\u0027d be gutting for something like 14 days.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-01-17T01:42:25Z\u0022 title=\u002201/17/2016 01:42  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 17, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Spaceception\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-17T02:08:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn October 12th 1915, an Astronomer by the name of Robert Innes found Proxima Centauri, a little over a century later, we\u0027re looking to see if there\u0027s a Habitable Exoplanet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://earthsky.org/space/this-date-in-science-discovery-of-proxima-centauri\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://earthsky.org/space/this-date-in-science-discovery-of-proxima-centauri\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Just Jim","CreatedById":148725,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-17T02:37:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222365811\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221452996523\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152800\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spaceception\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n27 minutes ago, Spaceception said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn October 12th 1915, an Astronomer by the name of Robert Innes found Proxima Centauri, a little over a century later, we\u0027re looking to see if there\u0027s a Habitable Exoplanet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://earthsky.org/space/this-date-in-science-discovery-of-proxima-centauri\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://earthsky.org/space/this-date-in-science-discovery-of-proxima-centauri\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhich, just by itself, is really, really cool!!!\u00A0\u00A0 We live in an amazing time for space exploration!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-17T02:59:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222365880\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221452998241\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022148725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Just Jim\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 minutes ago, Just Jim said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhich, just by itself, is really, really cool!!!\u00A0\u00A0 We live in an amazing time for space exploration!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYay!! Space!!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cubinator","CreatedById":150330,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-17T17:49:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe\u0027ll find planets, sure. But \u0022habitable\u0022 to me means you can take off your space helmet, take a deep breath, and not die from anything. I doubt we\u0027ll have the technology to determine whether or not a planet is actually habitable without actually going there anytime soon.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat said, finding exoplanets that are\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Eearthlike\u003C/em\u003E, meaning they have properties similar to Earth\u0027s like being in their star\u0027s habitable zone, is feasible in the near future. And that is really cool.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-17T18:00:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222366708\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221453052965\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150330\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022cubinator\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 1/17/2016 at 9:49 AM, cubinator said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe\u0027ll find planets, sure. But \u0022habitable\u0022 to me means you can take off your space helmet, take a deep breath, and not die from anything. I doubt we\u0027ll have the technology to determine whether or not a planet is actually habitable without actually going there anytime soon.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat said, finding exoplanets that are\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Eearthlike\u003C/em\u003E, meaning they have properties similar to Earth\u0027s like being in their star\u0027s habitable zone, is feasible in the near future. And that is really cool.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI put \u0022Potentially Habitable\u0022 on some of my first posts, but I just started doing \u0022Habitable\u0022 \u0027cause I thought people got the memo that I didn\u0027t mean 100% Habitable:/ Otherwise, I agree, finding \u0022Habitable\u0022 Exoplanets is probably the coolest thing in Astronomy right now\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-01-19T14:04:06Z\u0022 title=\u002201/19/2016 02:04  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 19, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Spaceception\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"fredinno","CreatedById":143381,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-17T23:36:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222366708\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221453052965\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150330\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022cubinator\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, cubinator said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe\u0027ll find planets, sure. But \u0022habitable\u0022 to me means you can take off your space helmet, take a deep breath, and not die from anything. I doubt we\u0027ll have the technology to determine whether or not a planet is actually habitable without actually going there anytime soon.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat said, finding exoplanets that are\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Eearthlike\u003C/em\u003E, meaning they have properties similar to Earth\u0027s like being in their star\u0027s habitable zone, is feasible in the near future. And that is really cool.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe something like ATLAST might be able to do it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd why is Proxima Centauri labeled as a PALE red dot? It\u0027s not that pale.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-17T23:47:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222367376\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221453073817\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022143381\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022fredinno\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 minutes ago, fredinno said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe something like ATLAST might be able to do it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd why is Proxima Centauri labeled as a PALE red dot? It\u0027s not that pale.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s a reference to \u0022Pale Blue Dot\u0022. Also, I have an idea for a 7th moon around \u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan lang=\u0022en-ca\u0022\u003E\u003Cfont color=\u0022#000000\u0022\u003EPersephone/Tyche, working on it now:)\u003C/font\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan lang=\u0022en-ca\u0022\u003E\u003Cfont color=\u0022#000000\u0022\u003E(Also, Proxima has almost no luminosity, other than infrared, which it has a lot of that)\u003C/font\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-01-17T23:47:55Z\u0022 title=\u002201/17/2016 11:47  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 17, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Spaceception\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HebaruSan","CreatedById":156657,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-18T01:40:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222365362\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221452986215\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002266349\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Motokid600\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 1/16/2016 at 5:16 PM, Motokid600 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo realistically what I\u0027d like to see is... Maybe a water world. Twice the size of Earth, no land mass and a thick atmosphere with a high ratio of oxygen.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003ESuper-Laythe ftw.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EOn that note, didn\u0027t Earth\u0027s \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Great_Oxygenation_Event\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Eoxygen come from early life\u003C/a\u003E? Do we know of other ways\u00A0to get a significant fraction of oxygen in an atmosphere, or are you saying you hope for a world with at least a \u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(37,37,37);font-family:sans-serif;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003Ecyanobacteria\u003C/span\u003E analogue?\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-18T01:43:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222367532\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221453081246\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022156657\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022HebaruSan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, HebaruSan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003ESuper-Laythe ftw.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EOn that note, didn\u0027t Earth\u0027s \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Great_Oxygenation_Event\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Eoxygen come from early life\u003C/a\u003E? Do we know of other ways\u00A0to get a significant fraction of oxygen in an atmosphere, or are you saying you hope for a world with at least a \u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(37,37,37);font-family:sans-serif;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003Ecyanobacteria\u003C/span\u003E analogue?\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYup. We want life, we may not find it, but we can still dream:)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"fredinno","CreatedById":143381,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-18T03:41:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222367394\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221453074426\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152800\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spaceception\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Spaceception said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s a reference to \u0022Pale Blue Dot\u0022. Also, I have an idea for a 7th moon around \u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan lang=\u0022en-ca\u0022\u003E\u003Cfont color=\u0022#000000\u0022\u003EPersephone/Tyche, working on it now:)\u003C/font\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan lang=\u0022en-ca\u0022\u003E\u003Cfont color=\u0022#000000\u0022\u003E(Also, Proxima has almost no luminosity, other than infrared, which it has a lot of that)\u003C/font\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wish I could fave you, but I\u0027m\u00A0out of points.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222367532\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221453081246\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022156657\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022HebaruSan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, HebaruSan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003ESuper-Laythe ftw.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EOn that note, didn\u0027t Earth\u0027s \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Great_Oxygenation_Event\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Eoxygen come from early life\u003C/a\u003E? Do we know of other ways\u00A0to get a significant fraction of oxygen in an atmosphere, or are you saying you hope for a world with at least a \u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(37,37,37);font-family:sans-serif;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003Ecyanobacteria\u003C/span\u003E analogue?\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe actually need O3, H2O, and CH4 in combination to be sure a place has life- O2 can be formed by solar wind breaking H2O, like on Venus.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-01-18T03:43:34Z\u0022 title=\u002201/18/2016 03:43  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 18, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by fredinno\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Findthepin1","CreatedById":139989,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-18T07:06:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI want to find a gas giant. I\u0027d be pleasantly surprised. If there was a gas giant in the system we\u0027d know about it by now.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"fredinno","CreatedById":143381,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-18T09:55:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222367846\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221453100782\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022139989\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Findthepin1\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Findthepin1 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI want to find a gas giant. I\u0027d be pleasantly surprised. If there was a gas giant in the system we\u0027d know about it by now.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot it was relatively far way, though. And it would likely be an ice giant of sorts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-19T04:55:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUpdate!!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPale red dot has begun it\u0027s planet search!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVery good weather conditions.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCheck out where the ESO telescopes are pointing: \u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.ls.eso.org/lasilla/dimm/lasc/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://www.ls.eso.org/lasilla/dimm/lasc/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-19T14:06:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nfirst spectrum of Proxima taken:D \u003Ca href=\u0022https://palereddot.org/first-spectrum-with-harps-live-from-la-silla/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://palereddot.org/first-spectrum-with-harps-live-from-la-silla/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"batman78781","CreatedById":156086,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-20T06:28:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe hype train has left the station!!!!!!!!! \u00A0Or maybe the hype observatory or something XD.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEither way, so stoked! Can\u0027t wait for results!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-20T15:09:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUpdate!!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://twitter.com/Pale_red_dot/status/689726701727813632\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022689726701727813632\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://twitter.com/Pale_red_dot/status/689726701727813632\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://twitter.com/Pale_red_dot\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022zJAq0pTz_bigger.jpg\u0022 src=\u0022https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/677553738668724224/zJAq0pTz_bigger.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPale Red Dot\u003C/strong\u003E \u003Cspan\u003E\u200F\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cs\u003E@\u003C/s\u003E\u003Cb\u003EPale_red_dot\u003C/b\u003E\u003C/span\u003E \u003C/a\u003E \u003Csmall\u003E \u003Ca href=\u0022https://twitter.com/Pale_red_dot/status/689734371142668289\u0022 title=\u00221:01 AM - 20 Jan 2016\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E6h\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E6 hours ago\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/a\u003E \u003C/small\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp lang=\u0022en\u0022\u003E\nSecond spectrum \u003Ca dir=\u0022ltr\u0022 href=\u0022https://twitter.com/hashtag/PaleRedDot?src=hash\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cs\u003E#\u003C/s\u003E\u003Cb\u003EPaleRedDot\u003C/b\u003E\u003C/a\u003E with HARPS \u003Ca dir=\u0022ltr\u0022 href=\u0022https://twitter.com/ESO\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cs\u003E@\u003C/s\u003E\u003Cb\u003Eeso\u003C/b\u003E\u003C/a\u003E. signal-to-noise at 650nm: 96.5 (Yesterday: 65.3) Much better tonight !!\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E \u003C/span\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\nIs Proxima really attached to Alpha Centauri? \u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.centauri-dreams.org/?p=34851\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://www.centauri-dreams.org/?p=34851\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-01-20T15:17:45Z\u0022 title=\u002201/20/2016 03:17  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 20, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Spaceception\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-22T13:49:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSmall post by Pale Red Dot \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://palereddot.org/stars/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://palereddot.org/stars/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-23T14:03:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUpdate!!!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInstruments and equipment needed\u00A0 maintenance, so no data over the past two days, but....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3rd spectrum taken last night! 57 more to go!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-25T13:16:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://twitter.com/Pale_red_dot/status/691556624285208580\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://twitter.com/Pale_red_dot/status/691556624285208580\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-01-25T13:16:36Z\u0022 title=\u002201/25/2016 01:16  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 25, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Spaceception\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Matuchkin","CreatedById":135127,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-25T20:00:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe have actually found planets in the A-B-Proxima system! Alpha Centauri Bc. Not habitable though...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-01-25T20:05:09Z\u0022 title=\u002201/25/2016 08:05  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 25, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Matuchkin\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-25T20:07:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222378935\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221453752040\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022135127\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Matuchkin\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, Matuchkin said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe have actually found planets in the A-B-Proxima system! Alpha Centauri Bc. Not habitable though...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlpha Centauri Bb (4 day orbit) (Likely doesn\u0027t exist) and Bc (13 day orbit) (Probably exists).,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo planets around Alpha Centauri A (As far as we know),\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo planets around Proxima (As least for now).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Matuchkin","CreatedById":135127,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-25T20:11:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222378947\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221453752457\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152800\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spaceception\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Spaceception said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlpha Centauri Bb (4 day orbit) (Likely doesn\u0027t exist) and Bc (13 day orbit) (Probably exists).,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo planets around Alpha Centauri A (As far as we know),\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo planets around Proxima (As least for now).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, the planets around\u00A0Proxima and Centauri A don\u0027t quite matter, because the stars are in one triple\u00A0system...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-01-25T20:12:51Z\u0022 title=\u002201/25/2016 08:12  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 25, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Matuchkin\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}